    "FriendlyName": "Unreal Claude MCP",
    "Description": "Drive Unreal Engine 5.7 from Claude (or any MCP client) over a localhost TCP socket. The plugin exposes 71 native C++ handlers (the bundled Python bridge adds 29 more synthetic tools, for 100 total): arbitrary Python execution (one-shot, persistent session, file, and selection-bound), Blueprint introspection + compile, Widget tree + Widget Blueprint introspection and mutation, animation / skeletal-mesh / static-mesh / Niagara / landscape / physics-asset / data-table / curve / texture / data-asset / sound-class / sound-submix / audio-bus / material-function inspectors, audio introspection trio (sound cue + sound wave + sound attenuation), viewport and high-res screenshots, actor queries and authoring (spawn / transform / property / component / focus / delete), level loading, texture import and configuration, Output Log access, console-command execution and CVar read/write, asset-registry tag queries, full asset-lifecycle authoring (inspect / move / rename / duplicate / delete / fix-up-redirectors / bulk-delete), Level Sequence introspection + scaffolding (inspect / create / bind-actor), material-instance authoring (create / set-parameter / inspect-material / inspect-instance), an event-push bus with subscriptions, a long-running task pattern, and a headless mod/plugin .pak compiler that shells out to RunUAT. Bypasses UE Python reflection limits by calling native C++ APIs directly.",
